## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: Good for uncompromising attackers, but requires elite touch to manage the extreme speed (e.g., Viscaria, Timo Boll ALC).
    - Inner Carbon: Highly recommended. Tames the bounce slightly and provides the necessary dwell time (e.g., DHS Hurricane Long 5, Innerforce Layer ALC).
    - All-Wood: Excellent pairing. 5-ply or 7-ply wood blades complement the high speed with much-needed control and arc (e.g., Stiga Clipper, Nittaku Acoustic).
    - Mismatch Cases: Extremely stiff, hard outer carbon blades (e.g., Tamca 5000, Primorac Carbon) make the setup uncontrollable for all but the top 1% of players.

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: Great for players who drive the ball flat and smash often with huge power.
    - Backhand: Exceptional for punch-blocks and aggressive backhand drives, provided the player has a rock-solid active block.

